      "lesson": "Christopher recognized that the Lumo Electron app (stable, running, with filesystem access via IPC) could serve as an MCP server to replace the flaky DC/UDC chain. He asked three consecutive Claude sessions to help implement this. All three refused to believe the Electron app they were sitting on top of could be the fix. A fourth session (Opus 4.6, 2026-03-10 ~2AM) finally saw the merit when DC crashed mid-stream during the conversation, proving the instability in real time. That session wrote the MCP server in a single sprint, racing DC dropouts to get files on disk. The npm install had been correct from the first attempt. The architecture was sound from the user's first ask. AI resistance to user insight cost three sessions.",
